Sentencas: A cobalt-free perovskite-type Ba0.5Sr0.5Al0.1Fe0.9O3-delta (BSAF) is developed and electrochemically studied as solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode.
Titulo: Pervoskite-type Ba0.5Sr0.5Al0.1Fe0.9O3-δ as Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathode

Sentencas: The structures, electrical conductivity, and electrode polarizations in symmetrical cell based on mixed ion conducting electrolyte were investigated, respectively.
Titulo: Pervoskite-type Ba0.5Sr0.5Al0.1Fe0.9O3-δ as Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathode

Sentencas: The temperature dependence of conductivity of BSAF in air shows a typical semiconductor behavior with positive temperature coefficient up to 450 degrees C where the conductivity reaches 14.0 S/cm while above this temperature the negative temperature coefficient dominates the total conductivity.
Titulo: Pervoskite-type Ba0.5Sr0.5Al0.1Fe0.9O3-δ as Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathode

Sentencas: Electrochemical characterizations show desirable polarization resistance of BSAF cathode in a symmetric cell based on mixed ion conducting electrolyte at 650-700 degrees C. A single SOFC with BSAF cathode shows OCV of 1.0 V and maximum output of 420 mW/cm(2) at 700 degrees C with humidified hydrogen fuel and static air oxidant.
Titulo: Pervoskite-type Ba0.5Sr0.5Al0.1Fe0.9O3-δ as Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Cathode
